 The coordinates used in Eqs. ()-() hide
the physical interpretation of the solution. To understand the
physical properties of the solution we will introduce
progressively new coordinates more suitable to this propose,
following the approach of Kinnersley and Walker and
Ashtekar and Dray. Although the alternative
 approach of Bonnor simplifies in a way the interpretation, we
cannot use it were since the cosmological constant prevents such a
coordinate transformation into the Weyl form.

